# hirengarai.github.io

Personal academic website built with Jekyll.

## Structure

```
├── _config.yml          # Jekyll configuration
├── _layouts/            # Page templates
├── _includes/           # Reusable components
├── _sass/               # SCSS stylesheets
│   ├── _index.scss      # Home page styles
│   ├── _fun.scss        # Fun page styles
│   └── _personal.scss   # Personal page styles
├── _posts/              # Blog posts (if any)
├── assets/
│   ├── css/             # Compiled CSS
│   ├── js/              # JavaScript files
│   ├── images/          # Images
│   ├── audio/           # Audio files
│   ├── docs/            # Documents (CV, etc.)
│   ├── pictures/        # Photos
│   └── videos/          # Videos
├── personal/            # Personal section pages
├── index.html           # Homepage
├── fun.html             # Fun intro page
├── personal.html        # Personal hub
├── Gemfile              # Ruby dependencies
└── README.md
```

## Local Development

```bash
# Install dependencies
bundle install

# Run local server
bundle exec jekyll serve

# With live reload
bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload
```

Open http://localhost:4000

## Deployment

Push to GitHub and enable GitHub Pages in repository settings.
Site will be live at https://hirengarai.github.io

## Notes

- The HTML files contain inline styles and scripts for maximum compatibility
- SCSS files in _sass/ are available if you want to modularize styles later
- JS files in assets/js/ are available if you want to externalize scripts later
